com.yahoo.sketches.frequencies

Class HashMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yahoo.sketches.frequencies.HashMap
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HashMapReverseEfficient

    public abstract class HashMap
extends Object
    Abstract class for a hashmap data structure, which stores (key, value) pairs, and supports the following non-standard operations: decrement all values by a given amount, and purge all (key, value) pairs whose key is below a specified threshold.
    Author:
    Edo Liberty, Justin Thaler

    • Constructor Detail

      • HashMap

        public HashMap(int mapSize)
        Constructor will create arrays of length mapSize, which must be a power of two. This restriction was made to ensure fast hashing. The protected variable this.loadThreshold is then set to the largest value that will not overload the hash table.
        Parameters:
        mapSize - determines the number of cells in the arrays underlying the HashMap implementation. Must be a power of 2. The hash table will be expected to store LOAD_FACT * mapSize (key, value) pairs.

        public abstract void adjustOrPutValue(long key,
                                      long adjustAmount,
                                      long putAmount)
        Increments the value mapped to the key if the key is present in the map. Otherwise, the key is inserted with the putAmount.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the value to increment
        adjustAmount - the amount by which to increment the value
        putAmount - the value put into the map if the key is not present
